Aim-listed investment company Armadale Capital has appointed Amne Suedi to the board as a nonexecutive director, with immediate effect. Suedi, a legal professional, is the founder and CEO of Shikana Law Group, a law firm operating in Kenya, Zanzibar and Tanzania and headquartered in Dar es Salaam, and which provides legal and investment advice to foreign investors operating in Africa. “We are delighted to welcome Amne to the board at what continues to be a very exciting time in the company’s development. “Amne will provide the company with great value and counsel from her significant experience of working with and advising Africa-based investment companies,” said Armadale director Nick Johansen. Armadale’s primary focus is its investment in the Mahenge Liandu graphite project, in Tanzania, which the company expects to become a valuable mining asset.